Update the ClickUp task tracking in the org file.

## Target Location

The file is: ~/Dropbox/Documents/nbs-internal-guide/org-src/clients/FamilyReportingCorporation/familyreportingcorporation.org

The heading is: * Clickup Tasks

## Finding or Creating the Subheading

First, use the clickup skill to identify the current task you are working on. Then:

1. Search for an existing subheading under \`* Clickup Tasks\` where:
   - The heading name exactly matches the ClickUp task name
   - The properties drawer contains the ClickUp task ID (format: CU-xxxxxxx)

2. If no matching subheading exists, create one:
   - The heading name MUST be identical to the ClickUp task name
   - Add a properties drawer with :CLICKUP_ID: containing the task ID (CU-xxxxxxx)
   - Set the TODO state to NEXTACTION

Example structure:
\`\`\`org
** NEXTACTION Implement user authentication flow
:PROPERTIES:
:CLICKUP_ID: CU-86abc123
:END:
\`\`\`

## Updating the Subheading

The subheading contains ONE comment that represents the current running status of the task. This is NOT a log or history of updates. Each update REPLACES the previous comment entirely.

The comment summarizes progress since the last comment was added. Review the conversation history to determine what was accomplished in this session.

Use links liberally throughout the comment - link to files, commits, merge requests, documentation, or any other relevant resources.

## Rules

- Use ONLY the clickup skill. Do not use MCP tools directly.
- NEVER change the task status. It is always NEXTACTION. No exceptions.
- NEVER use any other format than described above.
- NEVER add a history or log. One comment, replaced each time.
- ALWAYS include relevant links.
